      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a collector-grade example of the high-revving S54 platform. The 3.2L inline-six features individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering 333 hp with surgical precision. This chassis has undergone a comprehensive subframe reinforcement and a VANOS bulletproofing, addressing the primary mechanical concerns of the E46 generation. Power is delivered through a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox to a variable M differential lock. The suspension remains tight with factory-spec bushings and dampers, while the exterior retains its original deep luster with no evidence of road rash or oxidation. The interior is equally pristine, featuring Nappa leather with no bolster wear, reflecting its meticulous maintenance and climate-controlled storage. This is a turn-key enthusiast vehicle with a fully documented service pedigree.",
